text: Gaëlle Deborah Enganamouit (born on 9 June 1992 in Yaoundé, Cameroon) is a Cameroonian association football midfielder and forward who currently plays for Eskilstuna United DFFhttp://damfotboll.com/nyheter/2013/12/eskilstuna- united-forstarker-fran-kamerun Swedish and the Cameroon women's national football team. She has also played for Lorema Yaoundé and ŽFK Spartak Subotica. She can play a variety of positions, but normally she plays as a midfielder or forward. == References == Category:1992 births Category:Living people Category:Cameroonian footballers Category:Association football forwards Category:People from Yaoundé
